<item><guid>https://www.idlewildlodge.org/posts/george-dauth/</guid><title>George Dauth</title><link>https://www.idlewildlodge.org/posts/george-dauth/</link><description>George Dauth was born in Westhofen, Germany on October 24, 1868. At the age of 15 he immigrated to the United States to join his siblings who were living in Colorado. When he arrived he started working for his brother Louis Dauth at his grocery in Fort Collins, and later at Louis&#039;s second grocery at Five Points in Denver. Gradually George gathered the resources to start his own business and in 1905 he opened his own grocery in downtown Greeley at 806 9th Street.</description><pubDate>Sat, 16 Jul 2022 14:14:08 +0000</pubDate></item>
